# CI/CD Pipeline Standards

> **Note:** Job names and matrix below are the target bar. The authoritative required checks are those defined in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` and `.github/branch-protection-main.json` — align changes with those files, not this aspirational list alone.

## CI must be green before merge — no exceptions

The following checks must all pass on every PR:

```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yml — required jobs
jobs:
  lint-go:      # golangci-lint with .golangci.yml config
  lint-python:  # ruff + mypy --strict
  lint-ts:      # eslint + tsc --noEmit
  lint-proto:   # buf lint + buf breaking
  test-unit:    # go test ./... (no -tags=integration)
  test-unit-py: # pytest -m unit
  test-integration:  # go test -tags=integration + pytest -m integration
  security-scan:     # trufflehog + govulncheck + pip-audit
  migration-smoke:   # apply all migrations; verify idempotent
  metrics-format:    # promtool check metrics against running service
  coverage-gate:     # fail if coverage drops below thresholds
```

## golangci-lint configuration — the enforced linters

```yaml
# .golangci.yml
linters:
  enable:
    - gocyclo       # cyclomatic complexity ≤ 8
    - gocognit      # cognitive complexity ≤ 10
    - funlen        # function lines ≤ 40
    - cyclop        # file lines ≤ 400
    - gocritic      # style + correctness
    - gosec         # security vulnerabilities
    - errcheck      # all errors checked
    - wrapcheck     # errors wrapped with context
    - godot         # doc comments end with period
    - exhaustive    # switch cases exhaustive
    - maintidx      # maintainability index ≥ 20
    - revive        # Go idioms
    - unused        # no dead code
    - godox         # no TODO/FIXME in merged code

linters-settings:
  gocyclo:
    min-complexity: 8
  gocognit:
    min-complexity: 10
  funlen:
    lines: 40
    statements: 30
```

## Python linting configuration

```toml
# pyproject.toml
[tool.ruff]
select = ["E", "F", "W", "C90", "I", "N", "UP", "ANN", "S", "BLE", "B", "A", "COM", "DTZ", "EM", "ISC", "PIE", "PT", "Q", "RET", "SIM", "TID", "ARG", "PTH", "ERA", "PL", "TRY", "RUF"]
ignore = []
line-length = 100
target-version = "py311"

[tool.ruff.mccabe]
max-complexity = 8

[tool.mypy]
strict = true
python_version = "3.11"
```

## No TODO/FIXME in merged code

```go
// WRONG — committed to main
// TODO: validate the org_id here
// FIXME: this is broken for edge case X

// RIGHT — create a GitHub issue, reference it if needed
// See: https://github.com/Rick1330/ibex-harness/issues/123
```

Use `godox` linter which fails CI if TODO/FIXME/HACK/XXX appears in merged code.

## Makefile — every target documented

```makefile
# WRONG — undocumented targets; no one knows what they do
build:
    go build ./...

# RIGHT — self-documenting with help target
.PHONY: build
build: ## Build all Go services for the current platform
    go build $(BUILD_FLAGS) ./services/...

.PHONY: help
help: ## Show this help
    @grep -E '^[a-zA-Z_-]+:.*?## .*$$' $(MAKEFILE_LIST) | \
        awk 'BEGIN {FS = ":.*?## "}; {printf "  \033[36m%-20s\033[0m %s\n", $$1, $$2}'
```
